---
import Layout from '../../../components/layout/Layout.astro';

const lang = 'en' as const;
const title = 'Las Caminantes';

const img1 = (await import('../../../assets/images/obras/las-caminantes/caminantes-mamu-01.jpg')).default;
---

<Layout
  lang={lang}
  title="Las Caminantes — Work"
  description="Las Caminantes (2024). Living installation — weeds, plants, Morse code, speaker, MAMU. Maria Elvira Escallon."
>

  <article class="work-page">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="work-page__header">
        <p class="label">Work / 013</p>
        <h1>{title}</h1>
        <p class="work-page__meta">2024 &nbsp;/&nbsp; Living installation — weeds, plants, Morse code, speaker &nbsp;/&nbsp; Variable dimensions</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Main gallery -->
      <div class="work-page__gallery">
        <img src={img1.src} alt="Las Caminantes — Weed garden growing inside MAMU gallery" loading="eager">
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="aspect-ratio:16/10;">[ Pending: Las Caminantes — Detail of plants and speaker emitting Morse code ]</div>
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="aspect-ratio:16/10;">[ Pending: Las Caminantes — Installation view at MAMU ]</div>
      </div>

      <!-- Text + Technical sheet -->
      <div class="work-page__body">
        <div class="work-page__text">

          <p class="curatorial">
            A garden of weeds growing inside the exhibition hall. The plants emit via Morse
            code a message: "In each inhalation we meet." The work transforms the museum
            space into a living ecosystem where the boundary between the cultivated and the
            wild, the institutional and the organic, is deliberately dissolved.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The title — <em>Las Caminantes</em> (The Walkers) — refers to the plants
            themselves, beings that move and migrate despite our perception of them as
            stationary. Weeds are plants that appear uninvited, that cross boundaries,
            that resist eradication — qualities that make them both resilient and marginal.
            By giving them a place inside the museum, Escallon elevates these overlooked
            organisms to the status of protagonists.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The Morse code message — "In each inhalation we meet" — refers to the
            fundamental biological exchange between humans and plants: we breathe what
            they exhale, and they absorb what we release. This invisible reciprocity,
            occurring with every breath, is the most intimate and constant encounter
            between species. The coded transmission makes this invisible exchange audible,
            translating a biological fact into a poetic declaration.
          </p>

          <h3 style="margin-top: var(--s4);">CONTEXT</h3>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            Presented at MAMU in 2024, <em>Las Caminantes</em> continues Escallon's
            exploration of the vegetal world begun in <em>Nuevas Floras</em> (2003) and
            developed in <em>Encuentros con Seres Notables</em> (2022). While those
            earlier works focused on the morphological and material kinship between humans
            and trees, here the relationship becomes atmospheric and respiratory — a
            shared chemistry that sustains both forms of life.
          </p>
        </div>

        <aside class="work-page__ficha">
          <h4>TECHNICAL SHEET</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            <strong>Las Caminantes</strong><br>
            2024<br><br>
            Living installation.<br>
            Weeds, plants, Morse code transmitter, speaker.<br><br>
            Variable dimensions<br>
            Site-specific, MAMU
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">EXHIBITIONS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            Encounters in the Dust Factory — MAMU, 2024
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">HOW TO CITE</h4>
          <div class="ficha" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">
            Escallon, M.E. (2024). <em>Las Caminantes</em>.
            Living installation. Available at:
            mariaelviraescallon.com/en/works/las-caminantes/
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>

</Layout>

<style>
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    }
</style>
